\"wrapper\">\n        <div class=\"post\">\n\n  <header class=\"post-header\">\n    <h1 class=\"post-title\">Hello World</h1>\n    <p class=\"post-meta\">Dec 3, 2014</p>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"post-content\">\n    <p>Hello. I see you\226\128\153ve managed to stumble upon my first post here. Honestly, I just wanted to get something out. <a href=\"http://github.com/jekyll/jekyll\">Jekyll</a> seems to be a sufficiently complex tool and, like most times I have my first experience. I suppose I expect most folks that due this sort of thing are domain experts, or at least think they are. Suffice to say, I am not. Mostly I just see some bit of new technology or new idea and seek to gorge myself on the documentation, try a few things out, and then just move on\226\128\166like a buffet. So in the interest of keeping this a correct introduction here is the proverbial hello world. </p>\n\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><code class=\"language-ocaml\" data-lang=\"ocaml\"><span class=\"k\">let</span> <span class=\"bp\">()</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">print_endline</span> <span class=\"s2\">&quot;Hello, world!&quot;</span></code></pre></div>\n\n<p>At any rate, one thing I\226\128\153ve been looking at recently has been <a href=\"http://openmirage.org/\">Mirage</a> and learning about how to setup a unikernel to run on a Xen instance in the cloud. If you see this, than I was probably successful and I\226\128\153ll do a follow up post with my experience. Otherwise, it probably won\226\128\153t matter much what I\226\128\153ve said here anyway. </p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n</div>\n\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <footer class=\"site-footer\">\n\n  <div class=\"wrapper\">\n\n    <h2 class=\"footer-heading\">A Set Of Certain Musings</h2>\n\n    <div class=\"footer-col-wrapper\">\n      <div class=\"footer-col  footer-col-1\">\n        <ul class=\"contact-list\">\n          <li>A Set Of Certain Musings</li>\n          <li><a href=\"mailto:\"></a></li>\n   