let d_34f153a4f613795f8202894d325b7ae4 = "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n\n  <head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <meta http-equiv=\"X-UA-Compatible\" content=\"IE=edge\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width initial-scale=1\">\n\n  <title>Hello Linode</title>\n  <meta name=\"description\" content=\"It has been almost a week since my last post and I\226\128\153ve been working on getting this blog setup on a Xen virtual machine. Most folks seem to be setting up thei...\">\n\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/css/main.css\">\n  <link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"http://christopherbothwell.com/ocaml/mirage/linode/2014/12/08/hello-linode.html\">\n  <link rel=\"alternate\" type=\"application/atom+xml\" title=\"A Set Of Certain Musings\" href=\"http://christopherbothwell.com/feed.xml\" />\n</head>\n\n\n  <body>\n\n    <header class=\"site-header\">\n\n  <div class=\"wrapper\">\n\n    <a class=\"site-title\" href=\"/\">A Set Of Certain Musings</a>\n\n    <nav class=\"site-nav\">\n      <a href=\"#\" class=\"menu-icon\">\n        <svg viewBox=\"0 0 18 15\">\n          <path fill=\"#424242\" d=\"M18,1.484c0,0.82-0.665,1.484-1.484,1.484H1.484C0.665,2.969,0,2.304,0,1.484l0,0C0,0.665,0.665,0,1.484,0 h15.031C17.335,0,18,0.665,18,1.484L18,1.484z\"/>\n          <path fill=\"#424242\" d=\"M18,7.516C18,8.335,17.335,9,16.516,9H1.484C0.665,9,0,8.335,0,7.516l0,0c0-0.82,0.665-1.484,1.484-1.484 h15.031C17.335,6.031,18,6.696,18,7.516L18,7.516z\"/>\n          <path fill=\"#424242\" d=\"M18,13.516C18,14.335,17.335,15,16.516,15H1.484C0.665,15,0,14.335,0,13.516l0,0 c0-0.82,0.665-1.484,1.484-1.484h15.031C17.335,12.031,18,12.696,18,13.516L18,13.516z\"/>\n        </svg>\n      </a>\n\n      <div class=\"trigger\">\n        \n          \n          <a class=\"page-link\" href=\"/about/\">About</a>\n          \n        \n          \n        \n          \n        \n          \n        \n      </div>\n    </nav>\n\n  </div>\n\n</header>\n\n\n    <div class=\"page-content\">\n      <div class=\"wrapper\">\n        <div class=\"post\">\n\n  <header class=\"post-header\">\n    <h1 class=\"post-title\">Hello Linode</h1>\n    <p class=\"post-meta\">Dec 8, 2014</p>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"post-content\">\n    <p>It has been almost a week since my last post and I\226\128\153ve been working on getting this blog setup on a Xen virtual machine. Most folks seem to be setting up their mirage kernels on Amazon\226\128\153s EC2 instances or their private Xen cloud platforms. I thought it might be nice to try it out on a different public clould/Xen provider. </p>\n\n<h3 id=\"linode-and-mirage\">Linode and Mirage</h3>\n\n<p>I haven\226\128\153t been able to find a walk through or tutorial on how to get Mirage set up on Lindoe. Linode provides a number of default Linux distributions which can be installed from a single within the control panel. However, like AWS, they provide a pv-grub instance which can be used to boot a custom distribution. The caveat is that there are quite a few more steps which need to be taken to get your Mirage kernel off the ground. </p>\n\n<p>The steps to getting this set up were pretty similar to the EC2 tutorial, however I encountered some major issues that were fixed by some minor tweaks of the steps. In the interest of time spent reading this post (also writing it) I won\226\128\153t go too much into what the specific problems were. Suffice to say the menu.lst needs to be a little bit different than what is shown for EC2 on the <a href=\"http://openmirage.org/wiki/xen-boot\">Mirage tutorial</a>. </p>\n\n<p>Also, I haven\226\128\153t yet worked out how to automate the installation. I\226\128\153m pretty sure it can work similarly by installing a Linux distribution and then rsyncing in the kernel but I found that I could get the entire Mirage kernel installed on Linode without having to install a separate Linux distribution on the same node and I\226\128\153d like to keep that as a feature. Again, I haven\226\128\153t gotten the