let d_faaae317d899caec1e299cc99d0138ee = "&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;~&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;status&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;:`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nc&quot;&gt;OK&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;~&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;body&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;bp&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; \n    &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;with&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;exn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; \n      &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;try_lwt&lt;/span&gt; \n        &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;read_fs&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;path&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;^&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;/index.html&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; \n        &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;body&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; \n        &lt;span class=&quot;nn&quot;&gt;S&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;respond_string&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;~&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;status&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;:`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nc&quot;&gt;OK&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;~&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;body&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;bp&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; \n      &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;with&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;exn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nn&quot;&gt;S&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;respond_not_found&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;bp&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; \n&lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;in&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;There you have it. Now that &lt;a href=&quot;/about/&quot;&gt;about&lt;/a&gt; works I\226\128\153ll see about getting this blog up on the cloud. \226\128\152Til next time. &lt;/p&gt;\n</description>\n        <pubDate>Wed, 03 Dec 2014 09:57:47 -0600</pubDate>\n        <link>http://christopherbothwell.com/ocaml/mirage/2014/12/03/about-not-found.html</link>\n        <guid isPermaLink=\"true\">http://christopherbothwell.com/ocaml/mirage/2014/12/03/about-not-found.html</guid>\n        \n        \n        <category>ocaml</category>\n        \n        <category>mirage</category>\n        \n      </item>\n    \n      <item>\n        <title>Hello World</title>\n        <description>&lt;p&gt;Hello. I see you\226\128\153ve managed to stumble upon my first post here. Honestly, I just wanted to get something out. &lt;a href=&quot;http://github.com/jekyll/jekyll&quot;&gt;Jekyll&lt;/a&gt; seems to be a sufficiently complex tool and, like most times I have my first experience. I suppose I expect most folks that due this sort of thing are domain experts, or at least think they are. Suffice to say, I am not. Mostly I just see some bit of new technology or new idea and seek to gorge myself on the documentation, try a few things out, and then just move on\226\128\166like a buffet. So in the interest of keeping this a correct introduction here is the proverbial hello world. &lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-ocaml&quot; data-lang=&quot;ocaml&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;bp&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;print_endline&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;Hello, world!&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;At any rate, one thing I\226\128\153ve been looking at recently has been &lt;a href=&quot;http://openmirage.org/&quot;&gt;Mirage&lt;/a&gt; and learning about how to setup a unikernel to run on a Xen instance in the cloud. If you see this, tha"
let d_3d7f07215d733e281c55bca9999d1ffc = "uld contain text similar to the following (NOTE: your mirage kernel may not have the same name but should generally end with .xen). You\226\128\153ll need to use nano or cat fu for this as that\226\128\153s what is installed on Finnix. You could also rsync this file over using similar instructions to getting the kernel on the server. &lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;cat &amp;gt; /media/boot/grub/menu.lst &lt;span class=&quot;s&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt; EOF&lt;/span&gt;\n&lt;span class=&quot;s&quot;&gt;&amp;gt; timeout 1&lt;/span&gt;\n&lt;span class=&quot;s&quot;&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;\n&lt;span class=&quot;s&quot;&gt;&amp;gt; title Mirage&lt;/span&gt;\n&lt;span class=&quot;s&quot;&gt;&amp;gt; root (hd0)&lt;/span&gt;\n&lt;span class=&quot;s&quot;&gt;&amp;gt; kernel /boot/mir-www.xen root=/dev/xvda ro quiet&lt;/span&gt;\n&lt;span class=&quot;s&quot;&gt;&amp;gt; EOF&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;After this is done we\226\128\153ll need to set up a root password and start ssh so we can get the Mirage kernel onto the Linode. &lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;passwd\nEnter new UNIX password: \nRetype new UNIX password: \npasswd: password updated successfully \n&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;service ssh start&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;Once ssh has started we can then rsync the kernel over ssh from our local work station. &lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;rsync -avPz mir-www.xen root@ip.address.ofyour.linode:/media/boot/&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;h3 id=&quot;its-alive&quot;&gt;It\226\128\153s Alive!&lt;/h3&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;After this is complete, go back to your Linode Dashboard (under the dashboard tab) and click &lt;code&gt;Reboot&lt;/code&gt;. If all goes well you should be able to navigate to your Linode\226\128\153s IP in a browser and see it serving a page. (NOTE: Linode recommends a swap partition and not having one will prompt a warring on the Dashboard. Since we aren\226\128\153t using Linux I don\226\128\153t believe that is too much of a concern.) &lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;At this point you know as much as I do about how to get started with Mirage on Linode. I\226\128\153m still learning a bit about Jekyll and getting images working was my lesson for the day. I\226\128\153ll see about getting some sort of comment system up as I\226\128\153m sure there may be some questions about how to do this. &lt;/p&gt;\n</description>\n        <pubDate>Mon, 08 Dec 2014 05:31:44 -0600</pubDate>\n        <link>http://christopherbothwell.com/ocaml/mirage/linode/2014/12/08/hello-linode.html</link>\n        <guid isPermaLink=\"true\">http://christopherbothwell.com/ocaml/mirage/linode/2014/12/08/hello-linode.html</guid>\n        \n        \n        <category>ocaml</category>\n        \n        <category>mirage</category>\n        \n        <category>linode</category>\n        \n      </item>\n    \n      <item>\n        <title>About Not Found</title>\n        <description>&lt;p&gt;After getting the blog set up initially running in Jekyll things seemed to be moving along smoothly to pushing this thing up to one of the various cloud platforms which might support running a mirage unikernel. The next testing phase was to get this set up to run locally inside the Unix option on my workstation. &lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;h2 id=&quot;a-simple-mirage-project&quot;&gt;A Simple Mirage Project&lt;/h2&gt;\n\n&lt;p&gt;The mirage project suggests starting with the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/mirage/mirage-skeleton&quot;&gt;mirage-skeleton&lt;/a&gt; project to build some example unikernels. Basic work in getting the examples built can be found on the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.openmirage.org/wiki/hello-world&quot;&gt;mirage website&lt;/a&gt;. Mirage leverages the"
