let d_56e08ec029d308b921971942767227cf = "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n\n  <head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <meta http-equiv=\"X-UA-Compatible\" content=\"IE=edge\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width initial-scale=1\">\n\n  <title>About Not Found</title>\n  <meta name=\"description\" content=\"After getting the blog set up initially running in Jekyll things seemed to be moving along smoothly to pushing this thing up to one of the various cloud plat...\">\n\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/css/main.css\">\n  <link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"http://christopherbothwell.com/ocaml/mirage/2014/12/03/about-not-found.html\">\n  <link rel=\"alternate\" type=\"application/atom+xml\" title=\"A Set Of Certain Musings\" href=\"http://christopherbothwell.com/feed.xml\" />\n</head>\n\n\n  <body>\n\n    <header class=\"site-header\">\n\n  <div class=\"wrapper\">\n\n    <a class=\"site-title\" href=\"/\">A Set Of Certain Musings</a>\n\n    <nav class=\"site-nav\">\n      <a href=\"#\" class=\"menu-icon\">\n        <svg viewBox=\"0 0 18 15\">\n          <path fill=\"#424242\" d=\"M18,1.484c0,0.82-0.665,1.484-1.484,1.484H1.484C0.665,2.969,0,2.304,0,1.484l0,0C0,0.665,0.665,0,1.484,0 h15.031C17.335,0,18,0.665,18,1.484L18,1.484z\"/>\n          <path fill=\"#424242\" d=\"M18,7.516C18,8.335,17.335,9,16.516,9H1.484C0.665,9,0,8.335,0,7.516l0,0c0-0.82,0.665-1.484,1.484-1.484 h15.031C17.335,6.031,18,6.696,18,7.516L18,7.516z\"/>\n          <path fill=\"#424242\" d=\"M18,13.516C18,14.335,17.335,15,16.516,15H1.484C0.665,15,0,14.335,0,13.516l0,0 c0-0.82,0.665-1.484,1.484-1.484h15.031C17.335,12.031,18,12.696,18,13.516L18,13.516z\"/>\n        </svg>\n      </a>\n\n      <div class=\"trigger\">\n        \n          \n          <a class=\"page-link\" href=\"/about/\">About</a>\n          \n        \n          \n        \n          \n        \n          \n        \n      </div>\n    </nav>\n\n  </div>\n\n</header>\n\n\n    <div class=\"page-content\">\n      <div class=\"wrapper\">\n        <div class=\"post\">\n\n  <header class=\"post-header\">\n    <h1 class=\"post-title\">About Not Found</h1>\n    <p class=\"post-meta\">Dec 3, 2014</p>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"post-content\">\n    <p>After getting the blog set up initially running in Jekyll things seemed to be moving along smoothly to pushing this thing up to one of the various cloud platforms which might support running a mirage unikernel. The next testing phase was to get this set up to run locally inside the Unix option on my workstation. </p>\n\n<h2 id=\"a-simple-mirage-project\">A Simple Mirage Project</h2>\n\n<p>The mirage project suggests starting with the <a href=\"https://github.com/mirage/mirage-skeleton\">mirage-skeleton</a> project to build some example unikernels. Basic work in getting the examples built can be found on the <a href=\"http://www.openmirage.org/wiki/hello-world\">mirage website</a>. Mirage leverages the powerful Ocaml module system, specifically <a href=\"https://realworldocaml.org/v1/en/html/functors.html\">functors</a> to abstract away the fact that you can use different backends. During the build phase environment variables and options can be passed to the <code>mirage</code> tool to set up specific backends\226\128\166 at least\226\128\166 I believe that\226\128\153s how it works. </p>\n\n<p>Ocaml is sufficiently different than the curly brace languages I\226\128\153m used to and Mirage still seems a bit like black magic right now, so my confidence about that being the case is appropriately limited. Kindly, however, there is a static_website folder from the mirage-skeleton project that contains a basic unikernel for serving html pages from the htdocs folder that can take a complied Jekyll site (really any static site) and serve it. </p>\n\n<p>After moving some files around and getting the basic project to build without my Jekyll site, it was time to try to get the static blog in that htdocs folder. Jekyll lets you configure a build directory from the _config.yml file, so I opted to let Jekyll do the work for me. I dumped my blog folder inside of a copy of the static_webstie folder and added a <code>destination: ../htdocs/</code> to the _config.yml file and ran the <code>jekyll build</code> command. </p>\n\n<p>Next I configured the project to build with the Unix option. </"
